I went to Door Dash today to have it delivered to me and I initially thought the half street location would deliver to me but I was sadly mistaken when I got my meal and found the uncooked pork meat and smelly pork meat was given to me in my order. I went here because the pictures on Instagram looked amazing. I was hungry so decided to give this place a try. I ordered to take out. I got the house fried rice and the popcorn chicken. Along with that I ordered some taro bubble tea. The first sip of the tea tasted like water with a drop of the tea flavoring. I had to ask to get it redone. When I got home I opened up my popcorn chicken, and it had a dark brown color. It tasted okay, way too fried for my liking, some pieces were borderline burned. The rice was ok as well. Overall, for the price, the quality of the food was not there. To top it all off the customer service was subpar. The hostess was on her phone while trying to take care of me. This is why she rushed to make my bubble tea... I do not recommend this place for takeout, maybe dine in you'll have a better service.
